    "run-past-sirens": {
      "id": "run-past-sirens",
      "text": "You both press your hands over your ears and run! The Sirens' singing becomes frantic, angry that their spell isn't working.\n\nYou make it to the other side of the chamber, but the Sirens call out: \"Wait! We weren't going to hurt you. We're trapped here too, by the Sphinx's magic. If you defeat her, we'll be free.\"\n\n\"Why should we believe you?\" {{PLAYER1_NAME}} asks cautiously.\n\n\"Because we'll give you a gift. The Sphinx has a weakness - she cannot resist a riddle she's never heard. If you create a new riddle, she must try to solve it before asking hers.\"\n\nThis is valuable information!\n\n*Mythological Twist: Not all creatures in Greek myths were purely evil. Many were cursed or trapped, just trying to survive.*",
      "choices": [
        {
          "text": "Thank the Sirens and continue",
          "nextNodeId": "after-sirens"
        }
      ]
    },
    "lyre-counter": {
      "id": "lyre-counter",
      "text": "{{PLAYER2_NAME}} pulls out Chiron's lyre and begins to play! The magical instrument creates music so pure that it interrupts the Sirens' spell.\n\nThe Sirens stop singing, amazed. \"That lyre... it carries the blessing of Chiron himself! You must be true heroes.\"\n\nTheir demeanor changes completely. \"We apologize for trying to enchant you. The Sphinx trapped us here with her magic. We sing to lure travelers because we're so lonely.\"\n\nThey give you a pearl. \"Take this. When the Sphinx asks her riddle, hold this pearl - it will help you think clearly. And remember: the Sphinx loves riddles so much that if you ask her one she can't solve, she must answer yours first.\"\n\n*Orpheus: The greatest musician in Greek mythology could charm anyone with his lyre - even the gods of the Underworld!*",
      "choices": [
        {
          "text": "Thank the Sirens and continue",
          "nextNodeId": "after-sirens"
        }
      ]
    },
    "beast-corridor": {
      "id": "beast-corridor",
      "text": "You follow the breathing sounds and find a large chamber. Inside is a massive creature - not the Minotaur, but something else. It has the head of a lion, body of a goat, and tail of a serpent.\n\n\"A Chimera!\" {{PLAYER2_NAME}} gasps.\n\nThe Chimera opens its eyes. Surprisingly, it doesn't attack. \"More visitors,\" it rumbles. \"Are you here to fight or to talk?\"\n\nThe creature seems old and tired rather than aggressive.\n\n*The Chimera: This fire-breathing monster was defeated by the hero Bellerophon, who rode the winged horse Pegasus. 'Chimera' now means any creature made of different animal parts!*",
      "choices": [
        {
          "text": "\"We just want to talk. We mean no harm.\"",
          "nextNodeId": "friendly-chimera"
        },
        {
          "text": "Prepare to defend yourselves",
          "nextNodeId": "chimera-misunderstanding"
        }
      ]
