    "friendly-chimera": {
      "id": "friendly-chimera",
      "text": "The Chimera relaxes. \"Finally, children with sense. Most heroes attack first and ask questions never.\"\n\nIt explains that it guards a shortcut through the Labyrinth. \"The Sphinx moved in and made this place her home. I don't like her - too many riddles - but I stay out of her way.\"\n\n\"If you want the shortcut, you must answer one question. Not a riddle, just a question: What have you learned about Greek myths on your journey?\"\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} thinks about all the stories you've heard - about wisdom, hubris, the gods, and heroes who used cleverness as much as strength.\n\n*Character Over Combat: Many Greek myths teach that understanding and respect can work better than fighting!*",
      "choices": [
        {
          "text": "\"Greek myths teach that wisdom and humility are as important as strength.\"",
          "nextNodeId": "chimera-pleased"
        },
        {
          "text": "\"We learned that heroes come in many forms and work together.\"",
          "nextNodeId": "chimera-pleased"
        }
      ]
