    "chimera-pleased": {
      "id": "chimera-pleased",
      "text": "The Chimera nods its lion head approvingly. \"Good answers. You've been paying attention to the stories, not just rushing through them.\"\n\nIt moves aside, revealing a passage. \"This leads to the Sphinx's chamber. One more warning: the Sphinx is proud. Don't just answer her riddle - outsmart her. That's the only way to truly defeat her.\"\n\nThe goat head adds, \"She's also afraid of being proven less clever than mortals. Use that.\"\n\nThe serpent tail hisses, \"And get my snacks back! She took all my mice!\"\n\nYou thank all three heads and proceed through the shortcut.\n\n*Three-Part Creatures: Greeks loved combining animals! Besides the Chimera, there was the hippocamp (horse+fish), griffin (eagle+lion), and many more.*",
      "choices": [
        {
          "text": "Proceed to the Sphinx's chamber",
