    "chimera-misunderstanding": {
      "id": "chimera-misunderstanding",
      "text": "You raise your defenses, and the Chimera sighs smoke from its nostrils. \"Always the same. Very well, if we must fight...\"\n\nBut before anyone attacks, {{PLAYER1_NAME}} lowers {{PLAYER1_HIS_HER}} guard. \"Wait! We don't have to fight. We're looking for the Sphinx, not trouble.\"\n\nThe Chimera pauses, surprised. \"You... stopped? Most heroes charge blindly. Perhaps you're different.\"\n\nIt settles back down. \"I'm tired of fighting. I've been down here for centuries. If you promise not to attack, I'll help you.\"\n\n*Conflict Resolution: Sometimes the bravest thing is knowing when NOT to fight!*",
      "choices": [
        {
          "text": "\"We promise. Can you help us find the Sphinx?\"",
          "nextNodeId": "friendly-chimera"
