    "trap-corridor": {
      "id": "trap-corridor",
      "text": "The silent corridor seems safe, but Daedalus designed this maze with traps! Suddenly, the floor tiles start shifting!\n\n\"It's a puzzle floor!\" {{PLAYER2_NAME}} realizes. The tiles have Greek letters on them, and only some are safe to step on.\n\nYou notice the safe tiles spell out words when stepped on in order. Looking carefully, you see they spell: \"SOFIA\" - the Greek word for wisdom!\n\nCarefully, you hop from S to O to F to I to A, and reach the other side safely.\n\n*Greek Alphabet: The Greek alphabet is one of the oldest in the world! Words like 'alphabet' come from the first two Greek letters: alpha and beta.*",
      "choices": [
        {
          "text": "Continue through the Labyrinth",
