    "sphinx-approach": {
      "id": "sphinx-approach",
      "text": "The chamber is enormous, lit by mysterious blue flames. On a raised platform sits the Sphinx - a magnificent creature with a lion's golden body, eagle's wings, and a woman's face. Athena's owl sits in a cage beside her.\n\n\"At last!\" the Sphinx purrs. \"I was wondering when someone would come for the owl. I am the Sphinx, keeper of riddles, guardian of secrets.\"\n\nShe stretches lazily. \"Here are the rules: I will ask you a riddle. Answer correctly, and you may take the owl. Answer wrong, and you remain here forever as stone statues.\"\n\nHer eyes gleam. \"Unless... you'd like to try something different?\"\n\n*The Sphinx: The most famous Sphinx is Egyptian, but the Greek Sphinx was different - more dangerous and loved riddles!*",
      "choices": [
        {
          "text": "\"Ask your riddle. We're ready.\"",
          "nextNodeId": "sphinx-riddle"
        },
        {
          "text": "\"What if WE ask YOU a riddle first?\"",
          "nextNodeId": "reverse-riddle"
