    "reverse-riddle": {
      "id": "reverse-riddle",
      "text": "The Sphinx's eyes widen with interest. \"YOU want to riddle ME? How delightful! Very well - if your riddle stumps me, I'll answer one of yours. If I solve it, you must answer TWO of mine.\"\n\nYou remember what the Sirens said - the Sphinx can't resist a new riddle.\n\n{{PLAYER1_NAME}} and {{PLAYER2_NAME}} whisper together, then ask: \"I am something people want to have less of, but when they have less of me, they feel like they have more. What am I?\"\n\nThe Sphinx thinks... and thinks... her tail swishes impatiently.\n\n\"Problems? No... Weight? Closer... Stress!\" She frowns. \"No, that's not quite right...\"\n\n*Creating Riddles: Good riddles use contradictions - things that seem impossible until you think differently!*",
      "choices": [
        {
          "text": "Wait for her to give up",
          "nextNodeId": "sphinx-stumped"
