    "sphinx-offer": {
      "id": "sphinx-offer",
      "text": "The Sphinx leans forward conspiratorially. \"I grow tired of the same old game. Riddle, answer, statue or freedom. So boring.\"\n\n\"What if instead, we had a conversation? Tell me - what have you learned on your journey here? What do the old myths mean to you?\"\n\nShe seems genuinely curious. Maybe she's lonely, trapped in this Labyrinth for eternity.\n\n\"If your answer pleases me, I may just give you the owl. I took it because I was bored, not because I needed it.\"\n\n*Character Development: Even mythological monsters can have feelings and reasons for their actions!*",
      "choices": [
        {
          "text": "Share what you've learned about Greek mythology",
          "nextNodeId": "sphinx-conversation"
