    "sphinx-conversation": {
      "id": "sphinx-conversation",
      "text": "You tell the Sphinx everything - about the Oracle's wisdom, Hermes' tricks, the Sirens' loneliness, and the Chimera's tiredness. About Chiron teaching that cleverness matters as much as strength, and about how the gods reward respect and punish pride.\n\n\"Most importantly,\" {{PLAYER2_NAME}} says, \"we learned that Greek myths aren't just old stories. They teach real lessons about being brave, being clever, and being kind.\"\n\nThe Sphinx is quiet for a long moment. When she speaks, her voice is soft.\n\n\"In three thousand years, no one has spoken to me like this. They all see a monster to defeat, not a being to understand.\"\n\nShe opens the owl's cage.\n\n*The Power of Empathy: Understanding others - even those who seem like enemies - is one of the most heroic things you can do!*",
      "choices": [
        {
          "text": "Thank the Sphinx and take the owl",
          "nextNodeId": "peaceful-ending"
        }
      ]
