    "sphinx-secret": {
      "id": "sphinx-secret",
      "text": "The Sphinx sighs deeply. \"I stole the owl because... I wanted company. The owl of wisdom was the only creature smart enough to have a real conversation with me.\"\n\n\"I've been alone in this Labyrinth for three thousand years. The Minotaur was terrible company - all he did was roar. At least the owl could discuss philosophy.\"\n\nShe looks genuinely sad. \"I know I have to return her. Athena's owl belongs with the goddess. But perhaps... you could visit sometimes? Tell me new riddles?\"\n\n{{PLAYER2_NAME}} feels sympathy for the lonely creature.\n\n*Loneliness in Myths: Many Greek monsters weren't evil - they were isolated and misunderstood!*",
      "choices": [
        {
