    "peaceful-ending": {
      "id": "peaceful-ending",
      "text": "\"We promise to visit,\" you tell the Sphinx. \"And we'll bring new riddles from the mortal world!\"\n\nThe Sphinx beams - literally glows with happiness. \"Then take the owl, heroes. You've given me something more valuable than I expected: friendship.\"\n\nShe even guides you out of the Labyrinth herself, showing you secret passages and hidden wonders along the way.\n\nWhen you return the owl to Athena's temple, the goddess appears in a shimmer of light.\n\n\"Not only did you retrieve my owl,\" she says proudly, \"you did it with wisdom AND compassion. You befriended a creature others only feared. THAT is true heroism.\"\n\nShe blesses you both: \"May you always find clever solutions, make unexpected friends, and remember that the greatest adventures are the ones where everyone wins.\"\n\n*Lesson Learned: True wisdom means understanding others and finding solutions where everyone benefits!*",
      "text2": "THE END\n\nYou returned Athena's owl, made a friend of the Sphinx, and proved that the best heroes use their hearts as much as their minds. The stories of {{BOTH_NAMES}} will be told for generations - the heroes who solved the Labyrinth with kindness!",
      "isEnding": true,
