    "winning-ending": {
      "id": "winning-ending",
      "text": "Following the golden thread of Ariadne, you wind your way back through the Labyrinth. The maze that seemed so confusing before now makes sense - each turn, each passage, each challenge was preparing you for the final test.\n\nYou emerge into bright Greek sunlight, the owl perched happily on {{PLAYER2_NAME}}'s shoulder. A rainbow arcs across the sky - Iris, the messenger goddess, signaling the gods' approval.\n\nWhen you return the owl to Athens, Athena's statue glows with warmth. \"Heroes of wisdom,\" her voice fills your minds. \"You faced the Labyrinth not with swords, but with wit. You answered riddles, made allies, and showed that knowledge is the greatest weapon.\"\n\nShe grants you each a blessing: perfect memory and the ability to solve any puzzle. \"Go forth, young ones. May your adventures always lead to wisdom!\"\n\n*Hero's Journey Complete: You've learned that Greek mythology teaches timeless lessons about courage, cleverness, and character!*",
      "text2": "THE END\n\nCongratulations, {{BOTH_NAMES}}! You navigated the Labyrinth, outsmarted the Sphinx, and returned Athena's sacred owl. Along the way, you learned about Greek gods, heroes, and the ancient wisdom that still guides us today. Your names will join the legends!",
